ListAddVisibleAfterCall
/ End-to-end Pattern A live-ref check. set %products% to an empty list;
/ call AddProduct (which appends "apple" via list.add); assert the count
/ of %products% is 1 in the caller. Pattern A: list.add's plain-Data List
/ slot resolves to the caller's live %products% Data — mutation in the
/ called goal is visible to the caller because the list ref is shared.
/ Without Phase 5's Pattern A migration, list.add would Variables.Set a
/ fresh list and the caller's reference would still point at the stale
/ empty list.
- throw "not implemented"
